The paper discusses the management, harvesting, and organization of data on the Web, which are all topics related to databases and information retrieval. Therefore, cs.DB and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of XML and the Semantic Web, which are technologies commonly used in data management and artificial intelligence, respectively. Thus, cs.DL and cs.AI are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper touches on research avenues in these domains, which could fall under software engineering (cs.SE).
